        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 557 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from North Carolina Zoo to near
Pittsboro. Movement was south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sanford, Asheboro, Randleman, Pittsboro, Siler City, North Carolina
Zoo, Goldston, Liberty, Ramseur, and Franklinville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
